reviewText: YELLOWNECK (1954) is a Civil War-related picture that was originally shot in REPUBLIC's Trucolor process, but it's now only available in B&W.;Being set entirely in the Everglades, seeing a color version would be nice. Alas, Trucolor faded badly over time so the chances of that ever happening are near zero.This is essentially a five-man show starring Lin McCarthy, Stephen Courtleigh, Berry Kroeger, Harold Gordon and Bill Mason.A terrific story that in some ways is film noir.Courtleigh portrays an alcoholic Reb colonel who ran during the heat of battle. McCarthy is the level-headed sergeant and the man most likely to survive. Gordon's a big-mouthed, larceous, possibly homicidal Cockney who would steal your eye teeth, Kroeger has a collection of French "girlie" photos plus a small bag of gold that Gordon covets, and Mason is just "the Kid." Each deserted for his own reason and some of that is explored as the story unfolds.All of these Confederate AWOLs have letters stating that a sympathetic Seminole will guide them south to the ocean, where a British blockade runner awaits to ferry the fugitives to Cuba. As the five argue at their first meeting, a mortally wounded Indian stumbles upon them; he's the guide, murdered by his own people. So they have no choice but to blindly travel through miles of swamp, using only the sun as reference. This small group encounters many hazards: a tropical storm, alligators, rattlesnakes, a bobcat, malarial mosquitoes, hostile natives, quicksand. Most of them do not survive their ordeal.I really liked this film, especially its sad ending.

reviewText: I love all jungle action adventure movies & this movie portrays the American south Everglades as wild and adventurous as any other jungles around the world. This movie is well acted & shows a period of American history in a very entertaining way. I would love to see this as well as the movie "Winds across the Everglades" on D.V.D. I believe both movies portray times in American history in a accurate and entertaining way. This movie also streamed well with no glitches. The movie "Yellowneck" was a movie I was unaware of and found to be a rare gem!
